Class ProjectAddressHandler

java.lang.Object
ProjectAddressHandler
public class ProjectAddressHandler extends Object
This class contains methods which handles information regarding project addresses and their interactions with the database.

    • deleteProjectAddress

      public void deleteProjectAddress(ResultSet results, Statement statement, Project project, ProjectAddressHandler projectAddressHandler, Prompt prompt, String userInput, Scanner sc) throws SQLException
      Method which deletes a project address from the database. It checks if the project address is associated with a project, if so it will display the projects associated, otherwise it will ask if the user is sure they want to delete it. If so, the project address will be deleted from the database.
      Parameters:
      results - object to store information queried from the database
      statement - object to query and update the database
      project - project object
      projectAddressHandler - object which handles project addresses
      prompt - object containing prompts and processes user inputs
      userInput - the user's input
      sc - object to get user inputs
      Throws:
      SQLException - message for if an SQL error occurs
